reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely love these!
reviews.reviewText: These lights are so affordable and perfect if you want wall scounces without having to wire anything. They are rechargeable and come with a remote so they are easy to turn off and on. They are magnetic and stick to the inside of the shade. The shades are easy to hang and come with a sticky hook. The lights change color and are dimmable which is a very nice feature. The only downside is the battery life won’t last long if you keep them on for long periods of time. Other than that these are perfect!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good buy for the price.
reviews.reviewText: The sconces work well and look nice. The different colors are great for kids room. Easy to put together and hang.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love these lights!
reviews.reviewText: I really like these lights, but there are two downfalls. They aren’t very bright and they don’t stay charged up as long as I’d hoped. That’s the only reason why I gave them four stars, but I would definitely buy them again anyway. I also really like how you can change the colors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to decorate to your own style
reviews.reviewText: I thought these were pretty boring so I upcycled them by adding some old fabric I had in my sewing stuff. I used Liquid Stitch fabric glue (but any fabric glue will work). They are easy to do since the shade will lay completely flat, making it easy to make a pattern and to glue it all down. I added ribbon to the top part to finish the look and hide the frayed edges. They look gorgeous and now fit my boho lifestyle. And they look gorgeous when lit up and the rotating colors are displaying. (I love these lights, they are easy to set up, easy to move around and install, easy to recharge, easy easy easy!!!)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Mediocre Performance and Durability
reviews.reviewText: My experience with these lights has left me less than impressed. The adage "you get what you pay for" rings true in this case.The lighting options are disappointingly limited, offering only a BRIGHT white setting with no option to switch to a warmer tone. This lack of variety makes it challenging to create a cozy ambiance, limiting the overall appeal of these wall lights.Additionally, the choice of paper material for the lights is questionable. It bends and creases far too easily, compromising the aesthetic and durability of the product. It feels like a cheap material that doesn't live up to the standards I expected.If you're in search of versatile lighting with a durable build, I'd recommend looking elsewhere. These sconces fall short in both functionality and quality, making them a less-than-ideal choice for those seeking reliable battery-operated wall lights.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Nice lights but charge doesn’t hold well
reviews.reviewText: These are fine. They do the trick, are easy to mount and easy to charge. I find I have to charge them at least once a week so I wish the charge held longer. They also react to the remote of my firestick and other remote lights in the room which is a bit annoying

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great! Good value.
reviews.reviewText: I didn’t want to get lamps that would take up space on my dresser, so these were a perfect solution! The white is bright enough for me m..adjusts up a little bit. Also if you push the color button you can get to a warmer yellowish light. The remotes are cool but not sure if I use one per light or for both, seems to go either way. Still figuring this part out.Anyway, I had a vision for this wall with light sconces and now I have it! Very nice for a rental situation. I used the wall bracket to secure the lights. So happy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I realize the price was low but the quality of the sconce shade is extremely flimsy and one shade appears to be bigger than the other. Def feel the need to return them and try something else. I wanted “ light” feeling sconces but these are not doable
